A teenager at the weekend appeared at a Chief Magistratesâ€™ Court in Ikorodu, Lagos for allegedly stealing a conduit wire worth N16, 000. The police charged the 17 year-old-boy, whose address was not provided, with two counts of theft and breach of peace. Prosecuting Inspector John Iberedem told the court that the defendant allegedly committed the offences on January 4, at about 1:30am along Ijede road, Ikorodu. He said the defendant also conducted himself in a manner likely to cause a breach of the peace. According to Iberedem, the offence contravened sections 287 and 168(1) (d) of the Criminal Laws of Lagos State, 2015. The defendant pleaded not guilty. Chief Magistrate A. F. Azeez admitted the defendant to N5,000 bail with one surety in the like sum. Azeri adjourned the matter till July 7.